race.comment: THE BIG BLUE (5) six-start maiden who finds his race today despite drawing out. Was a month between runs when nailed late after sitting up on the speed to finish second over 1800m at this track. Fitter here and no excuses today. BLACK BABYLON (1) staying bred type who returned with an eye catching third over the mile here. Will go back from the draw and siege late. Each way. SWING STATE (12) covered ground in the run at his second race start when a fading fourth over 1500m at Kembla Grange. Has a poor set-up today but can run into the minor money. COOL DRINKS (10) stalked the pace when a plugging third over 1600m at Goulburn second-up. Map suits and sure to be thereabouts.
